  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "The macro environment is deteriorating with Bitcoin miners liquidating over 15,000 BTC in Q1 while oil prices hit 4-year highs amid Iran conflict escalation, threatening stagflation dynamics. The combination of crypto institutional selling pressure, geopolitical risk premium in energy markets, and upcoming tariff implementation is creating multiple headwinds for risk assets during what was expected to be an oversold relief rally.",
    "regimeImpact": "The bear market relief rally thesis is under severe pressure as oil approaches the $100 stagflation threshold while crypto shows institutional capitulation, suggesting the oversold bounce may be failing.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Tighten BMNR cash-secured put strikes closer to the $60,000 structural support as miner selling accelerates",
      "Increase short book exposure to growth-stage names most vulnerable to stagflation pressures from rising oil",
      "Rotate within Maturity overweight toward defensive sectors that benefit from higher energy prices"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Bitcoin miner capitulation with 15,000+ BTC sold in Q1 signals institutional stress and potential break of $60,000 support",
      "Oil at 4-year highs approaching $100 stagflation trigger while Iran conflict escalates",
      "Dollar strengthening on geopolitical risk creates additional headwinds for risk assets and crypto",
      "Ethereum testing critical $2,000 support with leverage setup suggesting volatility explosion ahead"
    ]
